  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6602.58 sitting just above the massive +170.3B gamma wall at 6600, dealers are actively selling into this rally as they hedge their long gamma positions. The PIN regime combined with the wall break and 77.9% GEX surge indicates dealers will aggressively fade moves away from 6600, creating strong magnetic pull back toward this level. Key resistance emerges at 6610 (+93.4B) while downside support sits at 6595 (flip level) - expect choppy action within this 6595-6610 range as dealers counteract directional moves.\n\n**Bottom line:** Price should get pulled back toward 6600 and stay range-bound between 6595-6610.",
